description: Linear Technology was a semiconductor company that specialized in analog integrated circuits. However, in 2017, Analog Devices acquired Linear Technology, and the brand  was phased out.

Notion is a software company known for its productivity and collaboration tool called Notion. Notion provides a platform that allows users to create, share, and manage notes, documents, databases, and more in a collaborative and customizable workspace.

Spline Studio LLC is a visual effects company based in Houston that offers 3D animation and rendering services. They specialize in the oil and gas industry and also offer concept development, motion graphics, and title design

Raycast is a privately held company that develops command bar software for developers to control their tools. Raycast is also a productivity app for Mac users that provides features and integrations to streamline workflows and increase productivity.

Loom is a video communication platform that allows users to record, share, and interact with videos. Loom's technology includes screen and camera recording, video editing, transcription, and the ability to share the recorded video link with others.

Trainline Group is a company that provides online train ticket booking services. Trainline allows users to book train tickets for various railway services across Europe. It offers a platform and mobile app that facilitate the planning, booking, and management of train journeys.
